* This Edric was a very remarkable person, and one of the last AnglaSaxon

patriots who held out against William the Conqueror. He only made his peace with the Normans in 1070, and he accompa- nied the king in his expedition to Scot- land in 1072. See an account of himin Ellis's Introduction to Domesday Book, vol. ii. p. 87. † The manor of Ledbury North has been long attached to the see of Hereford. This chapter gives a curious account of the manner in which the bishops became possessed of it. Itis mentioned in Domes- day as belonging to Edric the Wild.
